===message:I agree with your statement that a lot of Americans were misrepresented in the segment; however, this segment was accurate with the majority of Americans.  Your opinion was correct because it was your opinion, but the segment said that the majority of the Americans were experiencing what the segment represented.  A better life for everyone, more opportunities, poverty was on a decline, the world was exploding with better appliances.  Yes, even MY mom did not have a washing machine in her family growing up until late 60’s, but majority of the world was able to eventually purchase better everyday domestic devices.  I agree, many people were not represented, but do not have such a negative outlook on the program.  It was basically allowing us to see how our economy and our world exploded after the war.  How over production was not a problem anymore.  How Americans (as a whole) had a better life than other parts of the world.
