===message:I agree partly with your thoughts on the video. The point of view that those interviewed expressed in the video would be different from the point of view of those not as positively affected by the "boom-time". The reality, though, is that, by and large, almost everybody prospered in the 1950’s - not just the elite. In Levittown, New York, houses were being sold at an astonishing rate of 40 per day. The down payment was 100 dollars (hardly a number for the so-called elite). I appreciate your analogy and I agree with it’s validity. But, I think, the context of this video was attempting to convey the vast economic growth of the 1950’s...... not to examine American social flaws.
