===subject:Reply to Robert
===from:Stephenie Buice
===date:Tue Dec 10 22:03:11 2002
===message:I believe that there were several "groups" of people that did not prosper as well as might have been expected.  What is a $100 now, is much different than what a $100 was in 1950.  Not everyone had a hundred dollars for a down payment, let alone enough money to keep a household running.  And, even if you could afford a $100 down payment, your home was probably in the suburbs.  These individuals probably could not afford a car to commute to and from work.  Even though the American economy was prospering, does not mean that the "average" American was also.
=========yorg=========
