===message:I agree with your comment about leaving out a good segment  of people, mainly minorities.  This is a great amount of people to leave out, but in America, it's nothing new.  Minority groups were left out.  The Civil Rights Movement had not yet started.  African-Americans, Hispanics, Asians, as well as others, even women, had not yet began to receive their rights.  In the video, White Americans were shown as being prosperous after the war.  They were able to buy homes in the suburbs, make more money, and spend it as well.  Life was good in the 1950's, if you were one of the white Americans depicted in the video.
